		<td valign="top">
		<img src="images/page3.gif">
		<p><br>
		  In some respects I like this, even though
<br>
the workmanship's not great. Who'd rhyme 'today'
<br>
with 'day'? This one's arcane: what does it <em>say</em>?
<br>
Two down now; just two hundred more to go.
<br>
Call that a poem? Prose! And this one's so
<br>
<em>Poetic</em>. Why must people disobey
<br>
the basic rules of syntax? No. No way,
<br>
and No, and No, and No, and No, and No,
<br>
 
<br>
and......Oh. Here's something special: see it shine.
<br>
It coruscates: a lamp of burnished gold
<br>
revealing vistas formerly unseen.
<br>
I sense the presence of a noble soul
<br>
who dares to go where others have not been.
<br>
Ah, I recall it now: it's one of mine!
<br>
		</p>
		<br>
		<a class="byline" href="javascript:goauthor('anthony')">by David Anthony</a>
		</td></tr></table>
